pr_title: AC-984 : Delete Operation Offline Support for Allergy Respository.
pr_body:
<!--- Add a pull request title above in this format -->
<!--- real example: 'AC-204 Applying MVP Model' -->
<!--- 'AC-JiraIssueNumber JiraIssueTitle' -->

## Description of what I changed
<!--- Describe your changes in detail -->
<!--- It can simply be your commit message, which you must have -->
1. for updation and addition we cant have offline support since they need to fetch concepts on the fly to create or update allergies.
2. for deletion we can have offline support using workers since no such requirement exists.

## Issue I worked on
<!--- This project only accepts pull requests related to open issues -->
<!--- Want a new feature or change? Discuss it in an issue first -->
<!--- Found a bug? Point us to the issue/or create one so we can reproduce it -->

pr_title: AC-968/AC-969/AC-970: Fix Provider module offline support issues
pr_body:
<!--- Add a pull request title above in this format -->
<!--- real example: 'AC-204 Applying MVP Model' -->
<!--- 'AC-JiraIssueNumber JiraIssueTitle' -->

## Description of what I changed
<!--- Describe your changes in detail -->
<!--- It can simply be your commit message, which you must have -->
First, these 3 issues are related to each other and the same classes (and lines of code) need to be changed, so I've combined them in one PR for not producing merge conflicts.
1. Fixed provider's name being _[givenName givenName]_ instead of _[givenName familyName]_ in server when reconnecting to the internet. [AC-968]
2. Fixed AddProviderWorker being called forever even after success. [AC-969]
3. Fixed failing to edit or delete a newly created Provider in both online and offline modes. [AC-970]

When we create a Provider object in AddProviderWorker using the data passed to the worker, the passed _id_ is actually the __id_ NOT _id_. You can notice this in ProviderRepository in lines 140 and 146. So until now, _id_ field of this provider in the database table is empty. So we first, **updateProviderUuidById()** passing __id_ and the method searches in primary keys column _(_id)_ when connecting to the internet, then update the rest of the data of the provider in the database using **updateProviderByUuid()** which also updates the empty _id_ of the provider (not useful anyway because we already have __id_ value).
